This paper discusses conducting large experimental campaigns in programming languages research, which is a topic that falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper specifically focuses on using the Collective Knowledge framework, which is a tool for managing and sharing experimental workflows, making categories such as computer architecture (cs.AR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) relevant as well. Finally, the paper also discusses the ease of use and applicability of the framework, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) as it pertains to optimizing experimental workflows.
